definitions.definition: To perform or repeat an action on each item in a set.
examples: The max() function iterates through the data to find the highest value.

definitions.definition: To perform or repeat an action on the results of each such prior action.
examples: In mathematics, an iterated function is a function which is composed with itself, possibly ad infinitum, in a process called iteration.

definitions.definition: To utter or do a second time or many times; to repeat.
To repeat an activity, making incremental changes each time.

main_definition: ( computing ) To perform or repeat an action on each item in a set.
secondary_definitions: ( computing , mathematics ) To perform or repeat an action on the results of each such prior action.
( transitive , archaic ) To utter or do a second time or many times; to repeat.
( design , ambitransitive ) To repeat an activity, making incremental changes each time.
